               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350406-name-218" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-218" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-218" type="surname" value="WATERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-218" type="given" value="CHARLES HENRY"></interp>CHARLES HENRY WATERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am single, and life in Oxford-street—the prisoner attended there as charwoman—I missed artiolea which she had access to—she was at work there, and I accused her of it—she declared the had taken nothing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350406-name-219" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-219" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-219" type="surname" value="ASHLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-219" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES ASHLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. Aldon's of Berwick-street. I have two handkerchiefs, one of them was pawned by a boy, named John Smith, the other, by a woman whom I do not know, in the name of Mary Fowler.</p>
               <p>
